  "detailed_description": "<span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1443650/extras/e26485eb676526c3bf0a64812b9fe3d7.poster.avif?t=1766087740\" width=750 height=422 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1443650/extras/e26485eb676526c3bf0a64812b9fe3d7.webm?t=1766087740\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1443650/extras/e26485eb676526c3bf0a64812b9fe3d7.mp4?t=1766087740\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span><br><br><br>Dubbing Time is a game in which characters from 8 different parts are voiced and we wrote the scenario consisting of 8 parts. There are 4 themes in the game: Western, Heist, Gang, Cyber. And each theme has 2 parts. The stories of these episodes are linked.<br><br>Gameplay<br><br>Read the story of the episode first. Read the personal traits of the characters. Understand the character. Then write down your dialogs. Finish dubbing and watch your movies.",
  "about_the_game": "<span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1443650/extras/e26485eb676526c3bf0a64812b9fe3d7.poster.avif?t=1766087740\" width=750 height=422 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1443650/extras/e26485eb676526c3bf0a64812b9fe3d7.webm?t=1766087740\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1443650/extras/e26485eb676526c3bf0a64812b9fe3d7.mp4?t=1766087740\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span><br><br><br>Dubbing Time is a game in which characters from 8 different parts are voiced and we wrote the scenario consisting of 8 parts. There are 4 themes in the game: Western, Heist, Gang, Cyber. And each theme has 2 parts. The stories of these episodes are linked.<br><br>Gameplay<br><br>Read the story of the episode first. Read the personal traits of the characters. Understand the character. Then write down your dialogs. Finish dubbing and watch your movies.",
